Slight greenish tone today- no rain
Ice off on 4/23/95- late this year- (15th normally)
Loons are nesting- not many boats
Late ice off-4/28/96- no baby loons- two eagles over lake.  Top sample- no depth reported- assumed 1'.  Bottom sample- no depth reported- assumed 50'.
Ice out April 21- 1997. two loons hatched on 6/29.  Lots of rain and the lake level is okay.
Loons- 2 babies are big and diving- lots of pwc
Clear and no fish were caught on walleye opener.
Clear- loon on eggs- and 2" of rain on 6/4.
Clear- one baby loon- and 3" of rain on 7/25.
Clear and there are a lot of seagulls.
Did secchi on 7/7 and temp/DO on 7/9
No rain lately- low wind. Saw several loons and fish. Helped by daughter Erin.
Only took the temps - not secchi.  Lots of boat traffic on a perfect day.  Air temp was about 80 degress; calm wind.  Readings taken by Jill Balestri- Erika- and Courtney.
Warm mid-September day.  Calm and sunny.  No rain in weeks.
Lots of rain lately.  Not much boat traffic.  Aided by Erin Balestri.
Some rain in the morning.  Not ideal day for checking- but still a good reading.
Recent heavy rains.  Clear sky- calm water.  Lots of boat traffic- thoug.
Clear sky.  Light wind.  No rain in the previous few days (although a wet spring).
Nice day- quite a bit of boat traffic
Very clear and calm.  No rain in several days.  Light boat traffic.
Clear- calm day.  Normal boat traffic.  Had been a couple days since rain.
